Wash and dry produce. Core, deseed, and cut @long green pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and cut into ½-inch pieces). Drain @corn{1}(drained), then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).

Place @black beans{1%can} and their liquid in a #medium bowl{}; mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth (it's OK if they're still slightly chunky).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} (large pan for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and corn. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pepper is softened and corn is golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Add mashed beans and juice from half the lime. Season with @ground cumin{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans are warmed through and liquid is mostly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @Mexican cheese blend{½%cup}.

While black bean skillet cooks, trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(trimmed and root discarded); separate leaves and thinly slice.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp} and lime zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve black bean skillet directly from pan or divide between plates. Top with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz}(lightly crushed first) and lettuce in separate sections.

Drizzle lime crema over lettuce and serve with @hot sauce{1%tsp} and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For perfect balance, finish with a squeeze of lime juice right before serving!

Slice chicken against the grain. Place atop skillet along with tortilla chips and lettuce.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.